    en: "Rochester operates its own Examining Board of Plumbers. A plumber working in the city has to hold a Rochester plumber license before pulling any permit. Plumbing permits are separate from building permits and are filed through the city's CIVICS online portal. Rochester is unusual among large New York cities in allowing a homeowner to pull a plumbing permit and do the work on a home they own and occupy — New York City and Buffalo do not allow that. City plumbing inspectors perform the inspections directly; Rochester does not use third-party agencies for plumbing. Chapter 40 of the City Code sets the licensing framework."
